title: League won't launch.
body:
The first initial launch works but when I have to launch the login screen with the "Launch" button it does launch anything. When I open my task manager it says it is still running. I've tried running as admin, C:>Riot Games>League of Legends>RADS>projects and delete the lol_launcher and lol_patcher folders, tried going to C:\Riot Games\League of Legends and running lol.launcher.admin.exe, reinstalled twice, restarted computer and internet. Nothing works. 

For any possible spec reasons I have:
win 7 premium 64bit
i-7 2600K 3.4GHz (8 CPUs)
8gb ram
Nvidia GeFore GTX 580 4gb

help):

replies.body:
It sounds like your client may not be able to reach the servers properly, therefore not launching correctly. I recommend ensuring your local network settings are compatible with League by following our [networking guide.](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752664-Troubleshooting-Connection-Issues)

Let me know if your issue persists through those changes.
